- Reference compliance: "HIPAA", "SOX", "GLBA", "FACTA"
- Mention: "EPA Compliant", "NIST 800-88"

## Structured Data Requirements

### For Every Page

Include appropriate Schema.org markup:

- LocalBusiness for main pages
- Service for service pages
- AboutPage for about content
- ContactPage for contact information
- BreadcrumbList for navigation

### Service-Specific Schema

For service pages, include:

```json
{
  "@type": "Service",
  "name": "Service Name",
  "description": "Service description",
  "provider": {
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "name": "Computer Recyclers USA"
  },
  "areaServed": {
    "@type": "State",
    "name": "Georgia"
  }
}
```

## Performance & User Experience

### Page Speed Optimization

- Use Next.js Image component for all images
- Implement lazy loading for below-the-fold content
- Minimize JavaScript bundles
- Use CSS-in-JS or Tailwind for styling

### Mobile Optimization

- Ensure all content is mobile-responsive
- Test on various screen sizes
- Use touch-friendly buttons and links
- Optimize form inputs for mobile

### Accessibility

- Include proper ARIA labels
- Ensure sufficient color contrast
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide alternative text for all images

## Content Creation Guidelines

### Blog/Article Content

- Target long-tail keywords
- Include FAQ sections
- Add internal links to service pages
- Use schema markup for articles
- Include author information and publish dates

### Service Page Content

- Lead with customer benefits
- Include pricing information (if applicable)
- Add process explanations
- Include certifications and compliance info
- Add customer testimonials or case studies

### Landing Page Content

- Focus on single service or location
- Include multiple CTAs
- Add trust signals (certifications, testimonials)
- Use local keywords throughout
- Include contact information prominently

